[[Boeing 777-200ER]] suffered failure of its left ([[Aircraft engine position number|#1]]) engine, and a fire erupted.<ref name=\"ibt2276\">{{cite news |last=Lidgett |first=Adam |date=September 8, 2015 |title=British Airways Plane Fire Update: Runway 7L At Las Vegas Airport Reopens After Plane Fire That Left 14 People Injured |url=http://www.ibtimes.com/british-airways-plane-fire-update-runway-7l-las-vegas-airport-reopens-after-plane-2088015 |work=[[International Business Times]] |access-date=May 14, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160604103207/http://www.ibtimes.com/british-airways-plane-fire-update-runway-7l-las-vegas-airport-reopens-after-plane-2088015 |archive-date=June 4, 2016 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> 14 passengers suffered injuries during the evacuation,<ref name=\"ibt2276\" /> and the runway was closed for eight hours.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lewis |first=Rebecca |title=Runway reopens after British Airways plane catches fire at Las Vegas airport |url=http://www.ktnv.com/news/runway-reopens-after-british-airways-plane-catches-fire-at-las-vegas-airport |work=[[KTNV-TV]] |access-date=May 14, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603221151/http://www.ktnv.com/news/runway-reopens-after-british-airways-plane-catches-fire-at-las-vegas-airport |archive-date=2016-06-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The aircraft suffered major damage, but it was repaired and returned to service in March 2016.<ref>{{cite news |date=March 24, 2016 |title=British Airways B777-200ER G-VIIO Returns to Service |url=http://www.thebasource.com/british-airways-b777-200er-g-viio-returns-to-service/ |work=The BA Source |access-date=May 14, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160609201750/http://www.thebasource.com/british-airways-b777-200er-g-viio-returns-to-service/ |archive-date=June 9, 2016 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Noteslist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n;Bibliography\n{{Refbegin}}\n* {{cite report |last=Jones |first=Chris |date=2012 |title=Terminal 3 Media Kit |url=https://www.mccarran.com/T3-Information/files/t3%20press%20kit.pdf |publisher=McCarran International Airport |accessdate=May 1, 2016 |ref=harv |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325181650/https://www.mccarran.com/T3-Information/files/t3%20press%20kit.pdf |archivedate=March 25, 2016 }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Moehring |first1=Eugene |last2=Green |first2=Michael |date=2005 |title=Las Vegas: A Centennial History |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GQ7mORxm6TYC |location=Reno, NV |publisher=[[University of Nevada Press]] |isbn=0-87417-615-8 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Wright |first=Frank |date=2005 |title=Nevada Yesterdays: Short Looks at Las Vegas History |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VD0e59nXb6MC |location=Las Vegas, NV |publisher=Stephens Press |isbn=1-932173-27-7 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Zook |first1=Lynn |last2=Sandquist |first2=Allen |last3=Burke |first3=Carey |date=2009 |title=Las Vegas, 1905-1965 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MrDckUPM0nIC |publisher=[[Arcadia Publishing]] |isbn=978-0-7385-6969-7 |ref=harv}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons}}\n{{Wikivoyage}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.mccarran.com/}}\n* {{FAA-diagram|00662}}\n* {{FAA-procedures|LAS}}\n* [http://www.clarkcountynv.gov/Depts/parks/Pages/cannon-aviation-museum.aspx Howard W. Cannon Aviation Museum] {{mdash}} Official site\n* [[Jeppesen]] airport diagrams for [https://www.flickr.com/photos/12530375@N08/8041962050/sizes/l 1955] and [https://www.flickr.com/photos/12530375@N08/8066233386/sizes/l 1966]\n{{US-airport|LAS}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Aviation}}\n{{Major US Airports}}\n{{Las Vegas Valley}}\n{{Good article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mccarran International Airport}}\n[[Category:McCarran International Airport|*]]\n[[Category:1942 establishments in Nevada]]\n[[Category:Airports established in 1942]]\n[[Category:Airports in Clark County, Nevada]]\n[[Category:Buildings and struct