{"title_page": "Make It Right (BTS song)", "text_new": "{{short description|song by BTS}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Make It Right\n| type       = single\n| cover      = BTS - Make It Right.png\n| alt        =\n| language   = {{flatlist|\n* Korean\n* English\n}}\n| artist     = [[BTS (band)|BTS]] featuring [[Lauv]]\n| EP         = [[Map of the Soul: Persona]] ''and the album'' [[Map of the Soul: 7]]\n| released   = {{start date|2019|04|12}} (original)<br>{{start date|2019|10|18}} (Lauv version)\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   = \n| studio     =\n| genre      =\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[K-pop]]\n| length     = 3:42\n| label      = [[Big Hit Entertainment|Big Hit]]\n| writer     =\n* [[Fred Again|Fred Gibson]]\n* [[Ed Sheeran]]\n* Benjy Gibson\n* Jo Hill\n* [[RM (rapper)|RM]]\n* [[Suga (rapper)|Suga]]\n* [[J-Hope]]\n| producer   = Fred Gibson\n| chronology = [[BTS (band)|BTS]] singles\n| prev_title = [[Lights (BTS song)|Lights]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = [[Black Swan (BTS song)|Black Swan]]\n | next_year  = 2020\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Lauv]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = Sims\n | prev_year  = 2019\n | title      = Make It Right\n | year       = 2019\n | next_title = Mean It\n | next_year  = 2019\n}}\n {{External music video|{{YouTube| eXBu09fwe3I|\"Make It Right\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Make It Right'''\" is a song by South Korean boy band [[BTS (band)|BTS]]. It was released [[digital distribution|digitally]] on April 12, 2019, as part of the [[extended play]] ''[[Map of the Soul: Persona]]''. A collab featuring [[Lauv]] was released as the second single from the EP on October 18, 2019.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=BigHitEnt|number=1184756022881054720|title=<Make It Right (feat. Lauv)> \ubc1c\ub9e4 \uc548\ub0b4 #BTS #\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8 #MakeItRight|date=October 17, 2019|accessdate=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Background and release ==\nThe song was first teased by [[Suga (rapper)|Suga]] on [[Twitter]], showing an image of a track and tagging [[Ed Sheeran]] with \"This is for you.\" On April 11, a day before release, it was announced as the song Suga had teased in prior months.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Herman |first1=Tamar |title=BTS Announce Ed Sheeran Collaboration 'Make It Right |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bts/8506844/bts-ed-sheeran-collaboration-make-it-right |website=Billboard |accessdate=April 16, 2019 |date=April 11, 2019}}</ref> The title of the song appeared to recount [[Kim Seok-jin|Jin's]] monologue in the 2017 Love Yourself Highlight Reel during the band's Love Yourself era.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web |title=BTS - Make It Right |url=https://genius.com/Genius-translations-bts-make-it-right-english-translation-lyrics |website=[[Genius (website)|Genius]] |accessdate=April 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe album version of the song was released [[Music download|digitally]] on April 12, 2019.<ref name = \":2\">{{cite web |last1=Kim |first1=Jae-Ha |title=Album Review: BTS' 'Map of the Soul: Persona' |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/music/ct-ent-bts-map-of-the-soul-persona-review-20190412-story.html |website=[[Chicago Tribune]] |accessdate=April 19, 2019 |date=April 12, 2019}}</ref> The remixed version was teased on the group's and Lauv's social media platforms and officially released on October 18, 2019.\n\n== Promotion ==\nThe song was promoted on [[M Countdown]] April 19, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Herman |first1=Tamar |title=BTS Nail Debut Television Performance Of Ed Sheeran-Penned 'Make It Right': Watch |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bts/8507792/bts-perform-make-it-right-m-countdown-video |website=Billboard |accessdate=April 19, 2019 |date=April 19, 2019}}</ref> BTS also performed the original version of the song ''[[The Late Show with Stephen Colbert]]'' in May 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/05/bts-performance-colbert-late-show-interview|title=BTS Breaks into Song During Delightful Colbert Sit-Down, Stages Beatles-Inspired Performance\n|last=Bradley|first=Laura|date=May 16, 2019|magazine=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191213144327/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/05/bts-performance-colbert-late-show-interview|archive-date=December 13, 2019|url-status=live|access-date=December 13, 2019}}</ref> Additionally, BTS performed the song on [[Jingle Ball|iHeart Radio Jingle Ball]] and in [[New York City]]'s [[Times Square]] on ''[[Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve|Dick Clark\u2019s New Year\u2019s Rockin\u2019 Eve With Ryan Seacrest]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mtv.com/news/3148217/jingle-ball-2019-la-highlights/amp/|title=Camila's Red-Hot Romance, BTS's Surprise Guest And More Jingle Ball L.A. Highlights|last=Roth|first=Madeline|date=December 7, 2019|website=[[MTV|MTV News]]|url-status=live|access-date=December 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/bts-make-it-right-boy-with-luv-dick-clark-932815/|title=Watch BTS Perform \u2018Make It Right,\u2019 \u2018Boy With Luv\u2019 on \u2018Dick Clark\u2019|last=Zemler|first=Emily|date=January 2, 2020|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|url-status=live|access-date=January 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Composition and lyrics ==\n\"Make It Right\" has been described as a falsetto-vocal heavy [[contemporary R&B]] track that is, \"sung with a breathy, close-miked intensity that gives the curious illusion of intimacy.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/apr/12/bts-map-of-the-soul-persona-review|title=BTS: Map of the Soul: Persona \u2013 kings of K-pop are just another boyband|work=[[The Guardian]]|last=Petridis|first=Alexis|accessdate=April 16, 2019}}</ref> It uses a looped horn throughout the song, with ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' comparing it to [[Amerie]]'s \"[[1 Thing]]\" or [[Mario (American singer)|Mario]]'s \"[[Let Me Love You (Mario song)|Let Me Love You]]\" echoing sounds from the 2000s.<ref>{{cite web |last=Leight |first=Elias |title=BTS Establish a Holding Pattern on 'Map of the Soul: Persona' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/bts-map-of-the-soul-persona-review-822474/ |website=Rolling Stone |accessdate=April 16, 2019 |date=April 16, 2019}}</ref> It is backed with [[synthesizer|synthesizers]], and the lyrics talk about the wish to make the world better and improve relationships.<ref name=\":1\"/> It also speaks about their biggest accomplishments and that without their fans it would feel empty.<ref>{{cite web |last=Morin |first=Natalie |title=BTS Lets You Into Their Universe With Map of the Soul: Persona |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/04/229643/bts-map-of-the-soul-persona-album-review |website=[[Refinery29]] |accessdate=April 17, 2019}}</ref> [[Newsweek]] said although the topic of the song can be heavy, the instrumental is light.<ref>{{cite web |last=Wynne |first=Kelly |title=Every Song on BTS' New Album, 'Map of the Soul: Persona,' Ranked |url=https://www.newsweek.com/every-song-bts-new-album-map-soul-persona-ranked-1394392 |website=newsweek |accessdate=April 17, 2019 |date=April 12, 2019}}</ref> In the remixed version, [[Lauv]] replaces the Korean-language first verse with his own lyrics.\n\nThe remix version of the song is in the key of G major with 98 beats per minute while the original is G major with 106 beats per minute.<ref>{{cite web |title=BTS Song Search |url=https://tunebat.com/Search?q=bts |website=tunebat.com |accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n''[[The New York Times]]'' said about the track: \"It has some of [[Ed Sheeran]]'s signature soft-soul gestures, but BTS renders [it] with complexity,\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Caramanica |first1=Jon |title=The Playlist: BTS Expands Its Footprint, and 11 More New Songs |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/12/arts/music/playlist-bts-geko-yeasayer-courtney-barnett.html |website=The New York Times |accessdate=April 16, 2019 |date=April 12, 2019}}</ref> while Jae-ha Kim from the ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'' called it \"hopeful and optimistic\".<ref name = \":2\"/>\n\n== Credits and personnel ==\nThe song's original credits are adapted from the CD liner notes of ''[[Map of the Soul: Persona]]''.<ref>{{cite book |author1=BTS |title=Map of the Soul: Persona |date=April 12, 2019 |publisher=[[Big Hit Entertainment]] |location=South Korea}}</ref> [[Lauv]]'s credits as a songwriter on the remixed version are adapted from [[Spotify]].\n\n{{col-start}}{{col-2}}\n* [[BTS (band)|BTS]] \u2013 primary vocals\n*Fred \"FRED\" Gibson \u2013 producing, songwriting, drums, keyboard, synthesizer, programming\n*[[Ed Sheeran]] \u2013 songwriting\n*Benjy Gibson \u2013 songwriting\n*Jo Hill \u2013 songwriting\n*[[RM (rapper)|RM]] \u2013 songwriting, rap arrangement, recording engineer\n{{col-2}}\n*[[Suga (rapper)|Suga]] \u2013 songwriting\n*[[J-Hope]] \u2013 songwriting\n*[[Lauv|Ari Leff]] \u2013 songwriting (remixed single version only)\n*[[Jungkook]] \u2013 chorus\n*Pdogg \u2013 vocal arrangement, rap arrangement, recording engineer\n*Hiss Noise \u2013 recording engineer, digital engineer \n*El Capitxn \u2013 digital engineer\n{{col-end}}\n\n== Charts ==\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n=== Original version ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2019/4/aria-chart-watch-521/|title=ARIA Chart Watch #521|publisher=auspOp|date=April 20, 2019|accessdate=April 20, 2019}}</ref>\n| 89\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|72|artist=BTS|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 24, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|99|year=2019|week=43|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 30, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarysingle|15|year=2019|week=16|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 26, 2019}}\n|-\n{{singl