 ([[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]])\n|January 17, 2008\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |''[[Music Bank (TV series)|Music Bank]]'' ([[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]])\n|December 14, 2007\n|-\n|December 21, 2007\n|-\n|January 11, 2008\n|-\n|February 1, 2008\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|35em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{YouTube|id = ScorpVvqLwo |title = BIGBANG - \ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9 \uc778\uc0ac(LAST FAREWELL) M/V}}\n\n{{Big Bang singles}}\n\n[[Category:Big Bang (South Korean band) songs]]\n[[Category:YG Entertainment singles]]\n[[Category:Korean-language songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by G-Dragon]]\n[[Category:2007 singles]]\n[[Category:2007 songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Brave Brothers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Last Farewell\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Big Bang (South Korean band)|Big Bang]]\n| album      = [[Hot Issue (EP)|''Hot Issue'']]\n| released   = November 22, 2007\n| format     = {{hlist|[[CD single]]|[[Music download|digital download]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Electronic dance music]], [[pop music|pop]]\n| length     = 3:52\n| label      = [[YG Entertainment]]\n| writer     = [[G-Dragon]], [[Brave Brothers]]\n| producer   = [[G-Dragon]], [[Brave Brothers]]\n| prev_title = Always\n| prev_year  = 2007\n| next_title = How Gee\n| next_year  = 2008\n}}\n\n\"'''Last Farewell'''\" ([[Hangul|Korean]]: {{lang|ko|\ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9 \uc778\uc0ac}}; [[Revised Romanization of Korean|Revised Romanization]]: ''Majimak Insa'') is a song by [[South Korea]]n [[boy band]] [[Big Bang (South Korean band)|Big Bang]].  It was released through [[YG Entertainment]] on November 22, 2007 as the lead single from the quintet's second [[extended play]] [[Hot Issue (EP)|''Hot Issue'']].  The song was written by [[G-Dragon]] and composed by the member and [[Brave Brothers]].  Mirroring the success of the group's preceding single \"[[Lies (Big Bang song)|Lies]],\" the song went on to become a chart topper.\n\n== Background and composition ==\nWith the release of their first extended play, [[Always (EP)|''Always'']] in 2007, Big Bang began to experiment more with their sound, moving away from their original [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] roots, and experimenting with [[electronic music]] and [[dance music]]. Their second EP, ''[[Hot Issue (EP)|Hot Issue]]'', released that same year, built on that its predecessor's momentum.<ref name=\":0\"/> \"Last Farewell,\" the lead single, was described by [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] as one of the most blatant pop songs in the group's repertoire, with a \"trance-tinged hip pop\" sound.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/7633039/bigbang-best-songs|title=The 10 Best BIGBANG Songs: Critics' Picks|newspaper=Billboard|access-date=2017-01-19}}</ref> ''KpopStarz'' noted that the single included \"some of the clubbiest sounds seen from Big Bang up until this point\".<ref name=\"kpopstarz\"/> A Japanese-language version of the song named \"Baby Baby\" was included in the quintet's first and second Japanese albums ''[[Number 1 (Big Bang album)|Number 1]]'' and ''[[Big Bang (2009 album)|Big Bang]]'', as well in their [[greatest hits album]] ''[[The Best of Big Bang 2006-2014]]''. \n\n=== Controversies ===\nThe involvement of G-Dragon in writing and composing the melody \u2013 as it was unusual at the time for members of a band to be so involved in the production of their album<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2009/04/30/2009043000853.html|title=\uc591\ud604\uc11d, \ube45\ubc45 \uad8c\uc9c0\uc6a9 \uc791\uace1  \ub17c\ub780 \ud574\uba85|language=ko|access-date=2017-01-19}}</ref> \u2013 raised questions by [[netizen]]s over how much the rapper actually produced.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2009/04/30/2009043001315.html|title='\ube45\ubc45' \uc9c0\ub4dc\ub798\uace4(G-Dragon), \uc791\uace1 \uc2e4\ub825 \uacfc\uc7a5\ub41c \ud64d\ubcf4?|last=Kim|first=Young-ro|date=2009-04-30|work=The Chosun Ilbo|language=ko|access-date=2017-01-19|via=}}</ref>  [[Yang Hyun-suk]], founder and CEO of YG Entertainment, went on to clarify that G-Dragon wrote and compose the music, with arrangements done by long-time collaborator Brave Brothers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://h21.hani.co.kr/arti/culture/culture_general/24956.html|title=[\ub9c8\uc74c\uc740 \uc5b8\uc81c\ub098 \ub85d\uc2a4\ud0c0]\uc544\uc774\ub3cc \uc2a4\ud0c0\uc640 \u2018\uacf5\ub3d9 \uc791\uace1\uc790\u2019|last=Jeong|first=Minyoung|date=2009-05-13|website=|publisher=The Hankyoreh|language=ko|access-date=2017-01-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2009/08/this-artist-copied-big-bang|title=This Artist Copied Big Bang? {{!}} allkpop.com|newspaper=allkpop|access-date=2017-01-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2009/07/brave-brothers-album-to-feature-big-bang-and-son-dambi|title=Brave Brothers' Album to Feature Big Bang and Son Dambi {{!}} allkpop.com|newspaper=allkpop|access-date=2017-01-19}}</ref>\n\nThe success of Big Bang spawned the creation of OkBang, a Chinese group whose music and looks were similar to the former.<ref name=\"Copycat of Big Bang Surfaces in China\">{{cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/art/2009/12/135_57613.html|title=Copycat of Big Bang Surfaces in China|date=2009-12-20|author=|work=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=2008-03-10}}</ref>\n\n==Reception and recognition==\nReception for \"Last Farewell\" was positive, with Tamar Herman of ''Billboard'' ranking it at number nine in the magazine's list of ten best Big Bang songs, writing that the single \"hits all the right notes to be quintessential K-pop song: catchy chorus, swoon-worthy crooning, and a pump-up dance beat.\"<ref name=\":0\" /> Park Hyo-jae from ''[[The Chosun Ilbo]]'' praised its \"addictive chorus\" and \"sophisticated electronic sound\", commenting that the song being written by a member of the group set Big Bang apart from the other idols. Park also complimented the group's stage fashion, noting that their use of high top sneakers and skinny jeans, as well as their hair styles, had become a trend among teenagers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://choen.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2009/02/19/2009021901460.html|title=[\ube453 \uc544\uc774\ub3cc \uae30\ud68d\uc0ac \uc9d1\uc911 \ubd84\uc11d] \uc544\uc774\ub3cc\ub3c4 \uc2a4\uc2a4\ub85c \uc74c\uc545\uc744 \ub9cc\ub4e4\uc5b4\uc57c \ud55c\ub2e4. - \uc870\uc5d4 CHOEN|last=Park|first=Hyo-jae|date=2009-02-22|website=choen.chosun.com|publisher=The Chosun Ilbo|access-date=2017-01-19}}</ref> The single's choreography, especially the [[jump rope]] movement, became a national phenomenon in South Korea.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2007120811191544749&type=3 |title=\ube45\ubc45, '\uc904\ub118\uae30\ucda4'\uc73c\ub85c \uad6d\ubbfc\ub304\uc2a4 \ub3c4\uc804\n |work=Star News |date=December 8, 2007 |accessdate=December 21, 2017}}</ref> \"Last Farewell\" is recognized as one of the group's definitive songs, for setting the direction they would eventually go in on songs like \"[[Fantastic Baby]]\" and \"[[Bang Bang Bang (Big Bang song)|Bang Bang Bang]]\".<ref name=\":0\"/><ref name=\"kpopstarz\">{{citeweb|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/233485/20150823/big-bang-best-songs.htm|title=K-Pop Mixtape: 9 Most Definitive Big Bang Songs|accessdate=2017-02-16|website=KpopStarz.}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n\"Last Farewell\" was released prior to the creation of the [[Gaon Music Chart]], which began tracking music performance in 2010. The song topped various charts from online music services upon its release, including the [[Melon (online music service)|Melon]] chart for eight consecutive weeks, holding the record for longest-running number-one song by a boy group.<ref name=\"\ube45\ubc45 \uc96c\ud06c\uc628\ucc28\ud2b8 8\uc8fc \uc5f0\uc18d 1\uc704 \uae30\uc5fc, JOO\ub3c4 2\uc8fc\ub9cc\uc5d0 7\uc704 \uc9c4\uc785\">{{cite web|title=[M+\uae30\ud68d\u2026'\ubcf4\uc774\uadf8\ub8f9 \ud1b5\uacc4'\u2461] \ucd5c\uc7a5\u00b7\ucd5c\ub2e4 \uc74c\uc6d0 1\uc704 \ube45\ubc45, \uacac\uc904 \uadf8\ub8f9 \uc5c6\ub2e4 |last=Park |first=Jung Sun |work=MBN Daily|date=May 7, 2014 |url=http://www.mbn.co.kr/pages/news/newsView.php?news_seq_no=1778998 |accessdate=July 29, 2017 |language=ko  }}</ref> At another music service [[CJ E&M Music Performance Division|Mnet.com]], the single remained at the first spot for six weeks, a record for the time.<ref name=\"mnet\">{{citeweb|url= http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2008010809113244837&type=3|work=Star News |date=January 8, 2008 |accessdate=December 21, 2017|title=\ube45\ubc45, \uc2f8\uc774\uc6d4\ub4dc '\uc774\ub2ec\uc758\ub178\ub798' 3\uad00\uc655}}</ref> \"Last Farewell\" went to be awarded Song of the Month (December) in the 2008 [[Cyworld Digital Music Awards]], recording 170,000 copies sold that month.<ref name=\"mnet\"/><ref name=\"LFAREWELL/CYWORLD/SOM\"> {{cite web|url=http://music.cyworld.com/chart/chart_dma_list.asp?curMonth=200712|title=Song of the Month|year=2007|work=Cyworld|accessdate=2010-01-16|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110725172714/http://music.cyworld.com/chart/chart_dma_list.asp?curMonth=200712|archivedate=2011-07-25}}</ref> The single was the fourth best-performing song of the 2000's (decade) in Melon, the highest entry by a male group.<ref>{{citeweb|url =http://www.melon.com/chart/age/index.htm?chartType=AG&chartGenre=KPOP&chartDate=2000#params%5Bidx%5D=1 |title=The 2000's |accessdate=February 20, 2017 |publisher=Melon Music Chart}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Arrangement\n| title1 = Last Farewell\n| note1 = \ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9 \uc778\uc0ac; Majimak Insa<ref name=\":2\">{{citeweb|url=http://www.qobuz.com/fr-fr/album/hot-issue-bigbang/3610153734041 |title=Hot Issue - BIGBANG |work=[[Qobuz]]|accessdate=2017-02-28|language=fr}}</ref>\n| length1 = 3:52\n| lyrics1 = G-Dragon\n| music1 = G-Dragon, Brave Brothers\n| extra1 = Brave Brothers\n}}\n\n== Charts and sales ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-\n! Chart !! Peak<br />position  \n|-\n| [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet Music Chart]]\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 1<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://m.inews24.com/view.php?g_serial=305862&g_menu=700100|title=\uc544\uc774\ub274\uc2a424 \ubaa8\ubc14\uc77c|last=Bak|first=Jaedeok|date=2008-01-08|website=\uc544\uc774\ub274\uc2a424|publisher=Joy News|access-date=2017-01-20}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Melon Music Awards|Melon Music Chart]]\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 1<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n| [[Cyworld Digital Music Awards|Cyworld Music Chart]]\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 1<ref name=\":1\" />\n|}\n\n=== Sales ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!'''Chart'''\n!'''Sales'''\n|-\n|South Korea\n|5,128,203<ref>Cumulative sales for \"Last Farewell\" since 2011:\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?pageno=4&serviceGbn=S1020&termGbn=week&hitYear=2011&targetTime=12&nationGbn=K|title=Gaon Download Chart 2011 \u2013 Week  12|work=Gaon Chart|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161002073913/http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?pageno=4&serviceGbn=S1020&termGbn=week&hitYear=2011&targetTime=12&nationGbn=K |archivedate = October 2, 2016}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?pageno=4&serviceGbn=S1020&termGbn=week&hitYear=2011&targetTime=13&nationGbn=K|title=Gaon Download Chart 2011 \u2013 Week  13|work=Gaon Chart|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161002074401/http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?pageno=4&serviceGbn=S1020&termGbn=week&hitYear=2011&targetTime=13&nationGbn=K |archivedate = October 2, 2016}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?pageno=4&serviceGbn=S1020&termGbn=week&hitYear=2011&targetTime=29&nationGbn=K|title=Gaon Download Chart 2011 \u2013 Week  29|work=Gaon Chart|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/